# DAX Measures Documentation and clear explanation

This project uses DAX (Data Analysis Expressions) to create business metrics and perform advanced analytical calculations within Power BI. The measures were organized inside a dedicated Measures table to maintain a clean and scalable data model. The calculations support revenue analysis, profitability tracking, customer insights, time intelligence reporting, and variance analysis across multiple dashboard pages.

The Total Revenue measure calculates the overall sales generated from all transactions using the SalesAmount column from the Sales_Fact table.

DAX
Total Revenue = SUM(Sales_Fact[SalesAmount])


The Total Cost measure calculates the total operational or product cost associated with sales transactions.

DAX
Total Cost = SUM(Sales_Fact[CostAmount])

Gross Profit is derived by subtracting total cost from total revenue to measure overall profitability.

DAX
Gross Profit = [Total Revenue] - [Total Cost]

Gross Margin Percentage measures profitability efficiency by calculating the percentage of profit earned from total revenue.

DAX
Gross Margin % =
DIVIDE([Gross Profit], [Total Revenue])


The Total Orders measure calculates the total number of unique customer orders placed.

DAX
Total Orders =
DISTINCTCOUNT(Sales_Fact[OrderID])

Total Quantity calculates the total number of products sold across all transactions.

DAX
Total Quantity =
SUM(Sales_Fact[Quantity])


Average Order Value calculates the average revenue generated per order.

DAX
Average Order Value =
DIVIDE([Total Revenue], [Total Orders])


Previous Month Revenue uses time intelligence functions to retrieve revenue from the prior month for comparison analysis.

DAX
Previous Month Revenue =
CALCULATE(
    [Total Revenue],
    PREVIOUSMONTH(Date_Dimension[Date])
)


Revenue Change Percentage calculates month-over-month revenue growth or decline.

DAX
Revenue Change % =
DIVIDE(
    [Total Revenue] - [Previous Month Revenue],
    [Previous Month Revenue]
)

Revenue Difference calculates the numeric variance between current and previous month revenue.

DAX
Revenue Difference =
[Total Revenue] - [Previous Month Revenue]

Revenue YTD calculates cumulative revenue from the beginning of the year to the selected reporting period.

DAX
Revenue YTD =
TOTALYTD(
    [Total Revenue],
    Date_Dimension[Date]
)

Gross Profit YTD calculates cumulative gross profit over the current year.

DAX
Gross Profit YTD =
TOTALYTD(
    [Gross Profit],
    Date_Dimension[Date]
)

Revenue Contribution Percentage calculates the percentage contribution of each region, product, or category to total revenue.

DAX
Revenue Contribution % =
DIVIDE(
    [Total Revenue],
    CALCULATE(
        [Total Revenue],
        ALL(Region_Dimension)
    )
)

Low Margin Flag identifies products with low profitability and helps users quickly detect underperforming products during analysis.

DAX
Low Margin Flag =
IF([Gross Margin %] < 0.15, "Low Margin", "Healthy")


These DAX measures were used across KPI cards, trend charts, variance indicators, drill-through pages, and interactive business analysis dashboards to deliver meaningful insights and support data-driven decision-making.
